### Example Environment Variables for the 6 Second Scribbles Project

# VITE_BACKEND_HOST — optional. Controls where the frontend sends API + WebSocket traffic.
#
# LEAVE UNSET for any same-origin deploy (prod behind the Caddy/Cloudflare proxy).
# When unset, the frontend derives the backend from window.location:
#   - API  -> https://<page-host>   (same origin)
#   - WS   -> wss://<page-host>      (protocol follows the page: https -> wss)
# This is the correct prod setting: no hardcoded domain, no mixed content.
#
# SET IT ONLY when the backend is on a different host than the page (e.g. split
# local dev). Value is a WebSocket URL; the API host is derived by swapping ws->http.
# Use wss:// on any https page or the browser will flag mixed content.
#   VITE_BACKEND_HOST='wss://your-backend-domain.com'   # remote / https
#   VITE_BACKEND_HOST='ws://localhost:8000'             # local split dev
